modules.description: Provides functions to create, resolve, and chain asynchronous computations using promises. Operates on the `Lwt.t` type, enabling non-blocking I/O and cooperative multitasking. Used to handle HTTP requests with timeouts, manage event loops, and coordinate parallel file operations.

Provides access to configuration flags for debugging and strict sequence handling, using mutable boolean references. Works with global state to control runtime behavior of Lwt-based applications. Used to enable detailed logging during development and enforce strict execution order in asynchronous workflows.
